---
// About tab — bio with structured sections matching site design
const birthYear = 1980;
const birthMonth = 7; // August (0-indexed)
const now = new Date();
let age = now.getFullYear() - birthYear;
if (now.getMonth() < birthMonth) {
  age--;
}
---

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
  <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg text-[var(--color-accent)]">About Me</h2>

  <!-- Bio Card -->
  <div class="info-card p-5">
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
      My name's <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Steve</strong>, A.K.A
      <strong class="text-[var(--color-accent)]">TechXero/DarkXero</strong>, and I am a {age} year old
      Tech fanatic from <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Lebanon</strong>. I love technology,
      mainly Computer Hardware/Software, smartphones, and some web-design. I also love many music genres,
      like all types of Electronic mostly anything with hard bass, classic 80's, Heavy Metal, Country, among others.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Music Section -->
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm text-[var(--color-accent)] uppercase tracking-widest">
      Music
    </h3>
    <div class="info-card p-5">
      <div class="video-wrap">
        <iframe
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/NsBiI-LyVm4"
          title="About Me — Music"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
          allowfullscreen
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Films Section -->
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm text-[var(--color-accent)] uppercase tracking-widest">
      Films
    </h3>
    <div class="info-card p-5 space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        Films too, especially Art Films by famous Directors like
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Lars Von Trier</strong>,
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Tarkovsky</strong>,
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Kubrick</strong>,
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Francis Ford Coppola</strong>,
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">George Lucas</strong> and others.
        Don't get me wrong, I do like some of the commercial movies coming out today, but not all.
        These days they tend to do remakes rather than come up with new stuff...
      </p>
      <div class="video-wrap">
        <iframe
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6IZGwvxhXvw"
          title="About Me — Films"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
          allowfullscreen
        ></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Platforms Section -->
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm text-[var(--color-accent)] uppercase tracking-widest">
      Platforms
    </h3>
    <div class="info-card p-5">
      <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <img src="/ios-android.png" alt="iOS and Android" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card p-5 space-y-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        I am an avid <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">iOS</strong> user when it comes to smartphones.
        I did use <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Android</strong> for 5 years, was happy on it for a while,
        I moved to iOS and have been a happy man ever since. However, it's not to say that I will stick with it for good,
        who knows what the future holds? I might go back to Android... I use both in parallel now to see where I will land...
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        In essence, I am a <em class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)] not-italic font-medium">Multi-User</em> — I don't stick to one platform, I like to dabble in all of them,
        but my main passion is <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Linux</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Background -->
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm text-[var(--color-accent)] uppercase tracking-widest">
      Background
    </h3>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
      <div class="info-card p-4 space-y-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[var(--color-accent)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 13.255A23.931 23.931 0 0112 15c-3.183 0-6.22-.62-9-1.745M16 6V4a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v2m4 6h.01M5 20h14a2 2 0 002-2V8a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"/></svg>
          <h4 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Apple</h4>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">Landed a job at Apple in 2019 in Ireland. But it didn't last long unfortunately. At least I can say that I have worked for that company LoL...</p>
        <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-xs text-[var(--color-accent)]">Cork, Ireland &middot; 2019</span>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card p-4 space-y-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-[var(--color-accent)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10.325 4.317c.426-1.756 2.924-1.756 3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 002.573 1.066c1.543-.94 3.31.826 2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 001.066 2.573c1.756.426 1.756 2.924 0 3.35a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.066 2.573c.94 1.543-.826 3.31-2.37 2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.573 1.066c-.426 1.756-2.924 1.756-3.35 0a1.724 1.724 0 00-2.573-1.066c-1.543.94-3.31-.826-2.37-2.37a1.724 1.724 0 00-1.066-2.573c-1.756-.426-1.756-2.924 0-3.35a1.724 1.724 0 001.066-2.573c-.94-1.543.826-3.31 2.37-2.37.996.608 2.296.07 2.572-1.065z"/><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/></svg>
          <h4 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Freelance</h4>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">Freelance Technical Support specialist — I help people with their tech problems from time to time.</p>
        <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-xs text-[var(--color-accent)]">Lebanon &middot; Ongoing</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Passions -->
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-sm text-[var(--color-accent)] uppercase tracking-widest">
      Passions
    </h3>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
      {['Hardware Tinkering', 'Web Design', 'Open Source', 'Multi-Platform Workflows'].map((item) => (
        <div class="info-card p-4 text-center">
          <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">{item}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- XeroLinux -->
  <div class="info-card p-5">
    <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
      <img src="/xerolinux.png" alt="XeroLinux" class="w-full h-auto" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="info-card p-5">
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
      I currently maintain my very own ArchLinux Distro
      <a href="https://xerolinux.xyz" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
         class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent-light)] transition-colors hover:underline">XeroLinux</a>.
      An innovative Arch-based distribution designed to demystify the installation process while preserving user-driven customization.
      I mainly use it above any other OS because that's where my passion lies. <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">F.O.S.S</strong> is the way. You can quote me on that LoL...
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Desktop-only: Hacker Terminal -->
  <div class="hidden lg:flex lg:flex-col info-card p-4 overflow-hidden min-h-[280px]">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3 shrink-0">
      <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500/70"></span>
      <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/70"></span>
      <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500/70"></span>
      <span class="font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[10px] text-[var(--color-text-muted)] ml-2">root@stationxero:~#</span>
    </div>
    <div id="hacker-terminal" class="font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[11px] leading-[1.6] overflow-hidden flex-1">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

